properties.Name: VcfFormat
properties.Description:
These lines define the annotations contained in the FORMAT columns of the VCF and will be preceded by ##format.

If genotype data is present in the file, these are followed by a FORMAT column header, then an arbitrary number of sample IDs. The header line is tab-delimited.

Columns.Name: ReferenceFile
Columns.Description:
The version of the VCF specification to which the file conforms.

In the flat file received this line will begin with ##reference.

Columns.Name: GeneSequencingFileFormatId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a gene sequencing file format.

Columns.Name: FormatId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a format.

Columns.Name: FormatType
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a VCF Format Type.
